                      </div>
                          <header class="nbcnews-dc-header cf">
                            <h2 class="nbcnews-dc-heading"><a href="https://www.nbcnews.com/card/sen-warner-says-it-s-plausible-stone-told-trump-about-n977276">Sen. Warner says it&#x27;s &#x27;plausible&#x27; Stone told Trump about hacked emails in advance</a></h2>
                          </header>
                      <div itemprop="articleBody">
                                          <p> Democratic Sen. Mark Warner, the vice chairman of the Senate Intelligence Committee, told reporters earlier Wednesday that it's plausible that former Trump adviser Roger Stone told Trump in advance of hacked emails coming to light.  </p>
                                          <p> "To me it's very plausible that Roger Stone would relay that information to Donald Trump," Warner said, adding, "I think Mr. Cohen’s testimony is pretty compelling." </p>
                                          <p> Warner said Cohen spoke before the Senate Intelligence Committee for nine and half hours yesterday and characterized the testimony as "very, very important." He added that some of yesterday's testimony has been repeated today. </p>
                      </div>
