                      </div>
                          <header class="nbcnews-dc-header cf">
                            <h2 class="nbcnews-dc-heading"><a href="https://www.nbcnews.com/card/legal-analysis-cohen-acting-most-cooperating-witnesses-n977246">Legal analysis: Cohen acting like &#x27;most cooperating witnesses&#x27;</a></h2>
                          </header>
                      <div itemprop="articleBody">
                                          <p> Chuck Rosenberg, a former U.S. attorney and senior FBI official, says Cohen is acting like "most cooperating witnesses." </p>
                                          <p> "There is an interesting point about how prosecutors make cases: Prosecutors drill in on details, members of Congress don't seem to do that quite as much," Rosenberg told MSNBC's Katy Tur. </p>
                                          <p> "The details really matter," he said. "Cohen only has a small piece of it. He isn't overstating his case, he's not speculating, I'm not hearing conjecture from him," Rosenberg said. </p>
                                          <p> Rosenberg says Cohen clearly knows the information he provides to Congress has to be corroborated, but added, "I just don't think Congress is doing a very good job at corroborating it. Mueller will." </p>
                      </div>
